value: Resident [[i]kennicottii [/i]group] from south-coastal (west to Cordova) and southeastern Alaska, coastal and south-central British Columbia, northern Idaho, western and south-central Montana, northwestern Wyoming (Wind River Mountains), southeastern Colorado, and extreme western Oklahoma south to southern Baja California, central Sonora, in the Mexican highlands through central and eastern Chihuahua and Coahuila as far as the Distrito Federal, and to south-central Texas (east to Kerr County); and [[i]vinaceus [/i]group] in southern Sonora, western Chihuahua, and northern Sinaloa. Casual [[i]kennicottii [/i]group] in Alberta and Kansas (Morton Co.).
Woodland, especially oak and riparian woodland, and giant cacti (Subtropical and Temperate zones).
arid to semi-humid woodland, pine-oak, semi-open areas w.trees, riparian woods, cardon cactus
